.TH LOA-OBSIDIAN 1 "2026-03-23" "Library Of Alexandria" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
obsidian \- Show Obsidian integration status and usage
.SH SYNOPSIS
alexandria> obsidian
.SH DESCRIPTION
Displays the currently configured Obsidian vault path (if available) and
prints the available integration commands.
.br
Use this to quickly verify your setup before syncing or opening the vault.
.br
After sync, start daily work from \fBAlexandria/Dashboards/GUI Home.md\fR
and the \fBAlexandria/Bases/*.base\fR views.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
alexandria> obsidian
.TP
alexandria> obsidian sync
.TP
alexandria> obsidian doctor
.TP
alexandria> obsidian open
.TP
alexandria> obsidian open b0001
.SH SEE ALSO
loa(1), loa-export-obsidian(1), loa-obsidian-sync(1), loa-obsidian-doctor(1), loa-obsidian-open(1)
